title: For Sale:  Savage 99
postcontent: Savage Model 99 EG, manufactured in 1950. 24” medium weight tapered barrel, copper colored bead in raised ramp front sight, adjustable sporting rear sight & is chambered in .300 Savage. 5 round capacity. The serial number is 567,983, “B” lever boss code, manufactured in Chicopee Falls. It has the typical 99 features that made these a popular rifle; brass rotary carrier, cartridge counter, cocking indicator & a locking lever. These can be safely carried de-cocked with a live round in the chamber. Mechanically sound; functions correctly, the bore is excellent, bright, shiny with no frosting & the action is smooth & crisp. The rifle is numbers matching; receiver, forearm, butt stock & butt plate. The barrels on these were not serialized but the barrel address is correct for a 1950 gun. The stocks are walnut with nice grain & finish. Schnabel forearm, pistol grip with cap & hand cut checkering (the EG Model was checkered after 1940). There are no cracks or repairs, just minor handling marks & the checkering is still fairly sharp. The barrel retains almost all of its original bluing, the receiver & lever have turned a light Patina. There are no rust or pitting issues, no dings or dents, just minor handling marks. The receiver is tapped for a scope it must have once wore. The Savage 99 is a great hunting rifle with some nice features & the .300 Savage is a great round. I am the second owner. The first owner was a gentleman from the state of Washington. He purchased it in 1950 after serving in WW II. This was his personal hunting rifle for many years, but not fired often. He turned 85 recently and I purchased it. It has not been fired for over 20 years. New box of ammo goes with it.

For sale is a modified Bushmaster Carbon-15.  This is a super lightweight model weighing only 6 lbs!  Most rifles this size can weigh anywhere from 9 to 12 lbs and more depending on what is attached and this is only 6 lbs with the red dot attached.  The saved weight makes a huge difference when either carrying it around for any extended period of time, or when trying to speed up your movement and shooting.  I've used some rifles where my arms get tired and start to sway while aiming, but this rifle feels very easy to use and shoot.  

The handguard, grip, and stock have all been changed to Magpul parts in tan (FDE), which not only gives it a cool two tone look, but makes this rifle a very solid and light platform that is a pleasure to shoot.  This model is the optics ready carbine which leaves out the clumsy A2 style front sight base which leaves your sight picture clear of any obstructions.  Because of this I am selling it with the red dot sight in the pictures, as it is meant to be used with some kind of optic. 

This rifle features a true 5.56 NATO barrel which accepts both military 5.56 NATO and commercial .223 Remington ammunition. If you want to be able to shoot both, don't be fooled by some AR15's that shoot only the civilian commercial .223 only!  The 1/9 twist also means you can shoot the cheaper 55gr ammo as well as the match grade ammo (70gr +) with accurate results.

Uniflex shafts fall between Regular and Stiff, so they are best used by individuals whose drives range between 210 and 230 yards, whereas Stiff flex shafts are better handled by golfers with drives averaging more than 230 yards. Other factors in choosing flex include swing style and direction. Turf drag is no problem here; easier shots mean a much more enjoyable day on the course, as well as a better overall score. Furthermore, vibration and sound are dampened by the vibration-management cavity badge on each of the irons, making the clubs even more effective. The lack of vibration in the clubs will also be appreciated by golfers with bad backs and older individuals who want their drives to remain stable despite the constraints of a more mature body. In fact, golfers often find that the longer length of the shafts mean they hold their spines at a straighter angle, leading to a much more comfortable and productive swing.For golfers looking to improve their game without sacrificing style or compromising on value, the Inverted Cone golf club is an exceptional choice.
